shared_text:
Loyalsock Township Bands
December 4, 2019 at 9:00 PM ·

We are proud to share that 7 Loyalsock students have been selected by audition to represent the Township at the 2020 PMEA District 8 Band Festival! We are so proud of all of our students who auditioned and send a special congratulations to those who have been selected. All of the Loyalsock students who made the festival finished in the top 8 of their sections, including three first chairs, two second chairs, and one third chair. Congratulations!

Harrison Frear, alto saxophone (2nd)
Ian Hornberger, tuba (1st)
Emily Huskin, euphonium (1st)
David Hutchinson, trumpet (3rd)
Zackary Keller, tuba (2nd)
Brendan Kriner, trumpet (8th)
Collin Porter, trombone (1st)

Congratulations to all who auditioned! Your music making efforts fill us with #LancerPride.

The LTHS Drama Club invites all to come to their annual full-length play performance this weekend in the HS auditorium. This year's show is Neil Simon's "Rumors," even if that means making up ridiculous stories! The students in the cast and crew have put in a ton of work and hope to see many friendly faces in the audience!

Friday, December 6 @ 7:00pm
Saturday, December 7 @ 7:00pm
Sunday, December 8 @ 2:00pm

Adult tickets are $8 and student tickets are $6. Tickets can be purchased at the door.

post_text: Loyalsock Township is currently looking to fill a staff position at its After-School Program. The candidate must be motivated, energetic, and highly enjoy working with children. Work hours are Monday – Friday (Schick Elementary School Days Only) from 2:30pm – 5:45pm (start time could be flexible if needed) and from 12:30pm – 5:30pm on scheduled ½ days. The hourly rate is $10.00 per hour. If you are interested in applying, applications are available on our website at www.loyalsocktownshipbos.com or at the Loyalsock Recreation Office, 1607 Four Mile Drive, Williamsport, PA. If you have any questions please contact the Recreation Director at 570-567-7525.

The YMCA is looking for multiple volunteers for their Pumpkin Patch in the Pool event on October 18 from 5-7pm. A great silver cord opportunity for our students! #WhatsYourWhy #LancerPRIDE

Before the event 3pm-4:30pm
· 2 volunteers to clean the pumpkins
· 4 volunteers to decorate the community room & pool
During the event 5-7:30pm
· 1 volunteer to take photos
· 5 volunteers to get in the water with the kids & help pick out their pumpkin before they exit
· 6 volunteers to supervise/assist the kids decorating the pumpkins
· 2 volunteers to run the food & drink table
Tear down
4 volunteers for clean-up (7 to 7:30pm)

Come honor, remember and celebrate the life of Callie Cavanaugh this Saturday at her garden dedication! Bring a chair or buy a “Callie Strong” blanket to sit on and enjoy music and fun activities!

2:00 Formal Dedication concluding with over 100 butterflies release
3:00-5:00 Uptown Music Collective to Perform including many of Callie’s favorites
3:00-6:00 Activities, Food (Eat & Run, Sunset Ice Cream & Kettle Corn), and Vendors
6:00 Concert by Nashville’s and Loyalsock Native Dylan Rockoff
7:30 Glow Stick Light Vigil in Memory of and in Honor of Pediatric Cancer Kids

ACTIVITIES with Suggested Donation $5 Each to Benefit Callie Cares
Dunk a Lancer to Beat Cancer
Book Fairy Story Tent and Wand Making
Callie’s Silly Photo Booth
Bugs and Butterflies Face Painting, Twisted Garden Balloons, Make Your Own Butterfly House

post_text:
The Senate will honor the accomplishments of Coach Ron “CI” Insinger at the State Capitol today, April 9, 2019, at 1:00 p.m. Coach Insinger will be recognized in the Senate Chamber on his 1,000 career-win milestone. Having started his coaching career here at Loyalsock Township School District in 1974, Coach Insinger has since been inducted into the Lycoming County Sports Hall of Fame, Pennsylvania Sports Hall of Fame and Pennsylvania Basketball Hall of Fame.

To view the recognition LIVE, click the link below:
https://www.pasen.gov/Video/SenateVideo.cfm

post_text:
This Friday the Genetti will be hosting the Central PA Food Bank's annual Soup & A Bowl event. Patrons purchase a handmade bowl, enjoy a simple meal of soup and bread, and take home their bowl in the hopes that every time they take that empty bowl out of the cabinet they are reminded of all the empty bowls left in the world. The $ raised goes to the Food Bank. Mr. Kaplan and our visual art students crafted and glazed 25 bowls for this year's event!

There are seats at 11am, 1pm & 4:30pm with take-away lunch options. Tickets are $30 in advance & $35 at the door. Tickets can be bought here: https://www.eventbrite.com/e/central-pennsylvania-food-bank-2019-soup-and-a-bowl-tickets-53833853505?ref=estw
or via the link on the Central PA Food Bank's homepage.

post_text:
LTHS introduced the statewide Safe2Say Something initiative this week to students. Now you can anonymously share “tips” about disconcerting behavior you witness by contacting the hotline about ones health or well-being or awareness of suspicious behaviors or people around the school or any other time one might be in danger or in need of help.

Please download the app, visit the website, or call the # to share a tip. The hotline is open 24/7 and you may be asked some follow-up questions about the situation. Each report will also be sent to school administration and resource officers.

post_text: Reminder! It was decided at the September 12th School Board Meeting that there would be a K-12 Student Early Release/Dismissal on Friday, February 1st (Elem 12:15 pm; MS/HS 12:30 pm) for Teacher Professional Development in the afternoon.

post_text: LTHS students in good standing are encouraged to attend Student Government's Winter Formal on Saturday, February 16th from 8:00-10:30pm! We'll be recognizing Mr. Sock and our Snowball Princess/Queen! Presale tickets will be $5 or $10 at the door. Guest permission forms are in the high school office.
